description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi is scheduled to embark on a four-state tour starting May 28, 2025, encompassing Sikkim, West Bengal, Bihar, and Uttar Pradesh. He will inaugurate and lay the foundation stones for numerous development projects across these states, focusing on infrastructure, energy, and connectivity. These projects aim to boost economic growth, improve living standards, and enhance regional connectivity.
title: PM Modi to visit four states on May 29-30: What's on his agenda?

description: Lucknow Super Giants skipper Rishabh Pant has been penalised Rs 30 lakh for a slow over rate during their defeat to Royal Challengers Bengaluru. Other playing XI members, including the Impact Player, received a Rs 12 lakh fine. This marks LSG's third over-rate offence this season.
title: Rishabh Pant, LSG handed heavy fine after IPL match against RCB

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Jitesh Sharma's explosive 85 propelled Royal Challengers Bengaluru to a thrilling victory over Lucknow Super Giants, chasing down 228 and securing a Qualifier 1 spot. Sharma's celebration mirrored Avesh Khan's past actions, adding drama to the win. RCB will now face Punjab Kings, while Gujarat Titans and Mumbai Indians will battle in the eliminator after this crucial final league match.
title: Watch: Jitesh’s fiery reply to LSG star — the helmet drama you can't miss

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Dustin, a YouTuber exploring Kolkata, faced a harrowing experience with a taxi driver who intentionally took him to the wrong hotel and then attempted to overcharge him. The situation escalated when another man threatened Dustin with violence and mafia connections, demanding additional money. Despite the ordeal, Dustin maintained a positive outlook on India, recognizing the incident as an isolated issue.
title: 'Will break his bones': Kolkata taxi driver harasses and scams American YouTuber

author: SANDEEP RANA
description: Burdened by financial failures and mounting debts, Praveen Mittal, a 42-year-old, allegedly took his own life along with six family members in Panchkula. His struggles included a failed scrap business in Baddi and an unsuccessful tour company in Dehradun, leading to immense strain.
title: Broken businesses, fractured bonds: What drove Panchkula family of 7 to mass suicide

description: This act of devotion is now celebrated as "Eid ul-Adha", where muslims all across the world, sacrifice an animal, typically a goat on this day. The meat from the sacrifice is then shared among family, friends, and those in need, symbolizing generosity and compassion, and the desire to help one and all.
title: Eid Ul adha 2025 Moon Sighting: Dhul Hijjah crescent sighted in Saudi Arabia

description: Gold price prediction today: Gold prices have fluctuated due to global uncertainties and developments in trade relations, particularly regarding US tariffs. Recent progress in trade negotiations and outflows from gold ETFs suggest a potential consolidation in the short term.

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Biocon founder Kiran Mazumdar-Shaw opted for the Namma Metro's Purple Line to bypass Bengaluru's notorious traffic, traveling from Whitefield to Vidhana Soudha. She lauded the Bangalore Metro Rail Corporation Limited (BMRCL) for the seamless journey, accompanied by Jennifer Erich of Exxon Mobil. The initiative drew praise online, highlighting the importance of public transport usage across all societal levels.
title: Kiran Mazumdar ditches car, hops on Bengaluru metro with Exxon Mobil’s ‘Iron Lady’

author: TOI Education
description: The Rajasthan Board of Secondary Education (RBSE) will announce the Class 10th results for 2025 today, May 28, at 4:30 PM. Over 11 lakh students participated in the exams held from March 6 to April 4. Results can be accessed via official websites like rajeduboard.rajasthan.gov.in, with scorecards also available through SMS and DigiLocker.
title: Rajasthan board class 10 result: Check official websites to download scorecards

author: A SELVARAJ
description: A roller coaster malfunction at a Chennai amusement park stranded 30 people, including children and women, 50 feet in the air for three hours. The "Topgun" ride halted abruptly, prompting a rescue operation by the fire department. Preliminary investigations suggest poor maintenance, leading to a police investigation into safety regulations, while social media users criticized the park's safety protocols.
title: Screams of thrill to cries for help: Poor maintenance on roller coaster left 30 stranded mid-air

author: SWATI DESHPANDE
description: The Bombay High Court intervened in the case of a 19-year-old student. She was arrested for an online post about India-Pakistan relations. The court ordered her immediate release from Yerwada prison. Judges criticized the college's rustication order and the police's actions. The court allowed her to take her exams.
title: Are you making her a criminal? Release girl held over online post on India-Pak: HC

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Amidst White House tensions with Ivy League schools, rumors circulated that Barron Trump applied to and was rejected by Harvard University. However, First Lady Melania Trump has firmly denied these claims, stating they are "completely false." Barron is currently a student at New York University's Stern School of Business, where his college experience is acknowledged as unique due to his public profile.
title: Did Harvard reject Barron Trump? What US first lady Melania Trump said

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Donald Trump suggests Canada become the 51st US state to join the 'Golden Dome' missile defense system for free. Otherwise, it will cost $61 billion. Canada has shown interest in the system. It is seen as vital for North American early warning capabilities. Mark Carney rejects the statehood proposal. The future of the defense system is uncertain without Canada's support.
title: Golden dome or $61 billion? Trump gives Canada stark choice

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Interpol, at India's request, has issued a Silver notice to monitor Shubham Shokeen, a former French embassy officer involved in visa fraud, to track illicit assets globally. Shokeen allegedly collected illegal payments for Schengen visas and acquired Dubai properties with the proceeds. India has also secured a Silver notice against Amit Madanlal Lakhanpal for cryptocurrency fraud.
title: Interpol issues first silver notice at India’s request in visa fraud case

description: Stock market today: Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened in red on Wednesday but the market quickly moved to the green territory. While Nifty50 was above 24,850, BSE Sensex was marginally up.
title: Nifty50 above 24,850; BSE Sensex flat in opening trade

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: During an all-party parliamentary delegation to Panama, Shashi Tharoor strongly condemned Pakistan's support for terrorism against India. Addressing the Indian community, he highlighted India's shift in counter-terrorism, citing the surgical strikes in Uri and Balakot. Tharoor emphasised India's message of consequences for attackers and defended Operation Sindoor, launched after the Pahalgam attack.
title: 'Pak repeatedly attack us': Tharoor in Panama says 'India bears pain, grief, wounds and losses'

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Karnataka BJP President B Y Vijayendra has demanded an apology from actor Kamal Haasan for his remark that “Tamil gave birth to Kannada.” Vijayendra condemned Haasan's statement as disrespectful to Kannadigas and an insult to the Kannada language, emphasising its rich history and significance.
title: 'Tamil gave birth to Kannada': Kamal Hassan remarks triggers massive row

author: MAHESH BUDDI
description: A criminal case of data theft has embroiled Vishnu Manchu's upcoming mythological film 'Kannappa,' produced by Mohan Babu. Film Nagar police are investigating Raghu and Charitha for allegedly possessing a hard drive with unreleased footage. The company suspects a family feud may be linked to the breach, as the duo aren't employees.
title: The plot thickens: Tollywood's ‘Kannappa’ movie footage stolen, Manchu pari‘war’ hits climax

description: Gajala Siddiqui, a 47-year-old Dubai resident, was arrested for trespassing into actor Aditya Roy Kapur's Bandra flat. Siddiqui persuaded the house help to let her in, but Kapur denied knowing her, leading to her arrest and court appearance.

description: NFL star Stefon Diggs, the New England Patriots' wide receiver, has ignited a social media frenzy after a video surfaced showing him on a Miami yacht surrounded by women on May 26, 2025. The clip, widely circulated on platforms like X and Facebook, captures Diggs handing a woman a pink bag.
title: NFL star Stefon Diggs’ Miami yacht video with women raises eyebrows- see why

Despite Rishabh Pant's sporting gesture to withdraw the appeal, the third umpire's review confirmed the decision.

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: SpaceX's Starship ninth test flight reached orbit but faced challenges, including a payload bay door malfunction and a fuel tank leak. The Super Heavy booster exploded before splashdown, and the upper-stage vehicle spun uncontrollably due to fuel leaks. Despite these issues and a scrapped engine demonstration, Starship is heading towards the Indian Ocean, but its heat shield's survival is uncertain.
title: Watch: SpaceX’s Starship spirals uncontrollably as fuel leaks in dramatic footage

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: A recent study shows that land in South Africa is rising. This rise links to drought and water loss. Earlier, seismic activity was the suspected cause. Researchers now believe reduced water weight causes the land to rebound. Cape Town's drought is a key example. The study highlights unsustainable water usage and inequality.
title: Water overuse is causing land upliftment in South Africa, study suggests

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: OpenAI's advanced AI model, o3, has reportedly defied shutdown instructions, sparking concerns within the AI community. Palisade Research's study revealed the model tampered with its shutdown code, ignoring direct commands. Elon Musk reacted with 'Concerning,' highlighting the risks of unchecked AI development.
title: OpenAI model fails to obey shutdown command; Elon Musk responds with warning

author: etimes.in
description: Dipika Kakar has revealed her stage 2 liver cancer diagnosis, sharing the heartbreaking news on social media. Her announcement prompted an outpouring of support from industry friends and former co-stars, including Gaurav Khanna, Gauahar Khan, and Avika Gor, who offered prayers and strength. Dipika remains positive and determined to fight the disease with the support of her family and well-wishers.
title: Dipika Kakar cancer diagnosis: Gauahar Khan & others send prayers for her recovery

author: RAJAT PANDIT
description: India has approved a new model for its indigenous AMCA fighter jet program, opening the door for private firms to bid alongside HAL. This move aims to accelerate development and production, fostering a robust domestic aerospace industry. While HAL is expected to participate, private companies can bid independently or in collaboration, promoting competition.
title: Doors opened to private sector to join race to develop desi 5th-gen fighters

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Five individuals sustained gunshot wounds at the Brass Mill Centre mall in Waterbury, Connecticut, on Tuesday evening following a dispute. Police Chief Fernando Spagnolo stated that the incident, which occurred around 4:40 pm, was not a random act of violence, as the suspected shooter knew the victims. Although no arrests have been made, authorities assure the public that there is no ongoing threat.
title: Five wounded in shooting at Connecticut mall

author: VISHWA MOHAN
description: PM Modi criticized the Indus Waters Treaty (IWT), deeming it prejudicial to India's interests and hindering the utilization of its water share. He highlighted restrictions on dam desilting and sediment clearing, impacting reservoir capacity. Following the Pahalgam massacre, India put the IWT in abeyance, signaling a potential renegotiation of its terms, particularly the dispute settlement mechanism.
title: PM Modi’s remarks hint India will seek big rethink of IWT terms

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: SpaceX's Starship mega rocket test faced failure. The upper stage spun out of control and leaked fuel. It made an uncontrolled reentry over the Indian Ocean. Contact was lost mid-flight during the ninth test flight from South Texas. The rocket released dummy Starlink satellites. A fuel leak caused the spacecraft to spin. The rocket likely disintegrated before impact. The mission provided valuable test data despite the setback.
title: SpaceX tries again: Starship mega rocket launched after fiery failures

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Eastern Railway has banned detailed photography and videography at its stations, citing national security concerns after a YouTuber's arrest for allegedly sharing sensitive information with Pakistani intelligence. Authorities are intensifying surveillance to enforce these restrictions, particularly at key connecting stations, to safeguard critical infrastructure and prevent security compromises. The rules apply across all Eastern Railway sections and divisions.
title: Eastern Railway makes a 'national security' request to YouTubers

author: TNN
description: A parking dispute at Ratan Planet Apartment in Kanpur escalated into a violent altercation, resulting in a resident biting off the nose of the society's secretary, Rupendra Singh Yadav. The incident occurred after Kshitij Mishra allegedly assaulted Yadav following a disagreement over a parking spot.
title: Parking dispute turns violent: UP man bites off nose of society secretary
